doc.after: Classical antiquity also the classical era classical period or classical age is a broad term for a long period of cultural history centered on the Mediterranean Sea comprising the interlocking civilizations of ancient Greece and ancient Rome collectively known as the Greco Roman world It is the period in which Greek and Roman society flourished and wielded great influence throughout Europe North Africa and the Middle East
